## Contract testing (Pact)

This project uses [Pact](https://docs.pact.io/) for consumer-driven contract testing:

- **Consumer test** (`tests/functional/test_consumer_inventory.py`): runs the inventory client against a Pact mock server and writes `pacts/<app>-inventory.json`. Runs in the normal `test` CI job (functional tier, no real network).
- **Provider verification** (`tests/contract/test_provider_pact.py`): replays the committed example consumer pact (`pacts/examplewebapp-app.json`) against the running app + testcontainers Postgres. Runs in the gated `contracts` CI job.
- `task contract:pact` — run both locally.

**Pact Broker (opt-in):** set `PACT_BROKER_URL` + `PACT_BROKER_TOKEN` (GitHub repo secrets) to publish pacts and verify against a real broker. Without those secrets the `contracts` CI job uses local pact files only (`scripts/pact-publish.sh` no-ops). The multi-repo flow — consumer publishes, provider verifies broker pacts, `pact-broker can-i-deploy` gates releases — is documented in the script.
{%- endif %}
